  "updated_summary": "Archival footage from September 21, 2003, depicts a young Cristiano Ronaldo in a red Manchester United number 7 jersey skillfully dribbling past an Arsenal defender, though the narrator notes his \"skill to escape Arsenal's pressure\" was \"followed by a poor pass forward.\" A split-screen shows Roy Keane and Sir Alex Ferguson embracing Ronaldo, with the narrator explaining Ferguson treated the teenager uniquely, similar to Cantona. A quote from Roy Keane states, 'He was immediately one of the hardest working players at United,' and the narrator adds that Ferguson recognized Ronaldo's professional mindset despite tactical shortcomings. Ronaldo scored his first goal for United against Portsmouth via a free kick, as indicated by the on-screen text 'UNITED 3-0 P'MOUTH, RONALDO - 80’'. Early stats show 'UNTIL JANUARY, 19 CAPS, 11 STARTS', with Ronaldo participating in 19 matches and starting 11. The narrative mentions United's transitional period, their Champions League exit to Porto and Mourinho, and their third-place finish in the EPL 03/04 standings, with Ronaldo's growing impact evidenced by a goal against Chelsea."
